  <brief_title>Effect of Lidocaine Patch for Shoulder Pain in Laparoscopic Cholecystectomy</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Ajou University School of Medicine</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Ajou University School of Medicine</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary purpose of this study is to investigate the effect of lidocaine patch on the
      shoulder pain score after end of surgery.

      The secondary purpose of this study is to investigate the effect of lidocaine patch on the
      total number of analgesic request on ward.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
